com.google.gcloud.bigquery

Class ExternalDataConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.gcloud.bigquery.ExternalDataConfiguration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class ExternalDataConfiguration
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Google BigQuery configuration for tables backed by external data. Objects of this class describe the data format, location, and other properties of a table stored outside of BigQuery. By defining these properties, the data source can then be queried as if it were a standard BigQuery table. Support for external tables is experimental and might be subject to changes or removed.
    See Also:
    Federated Data Sources , Serialized Form

      • compression

        public String compression()

        See Also:

      • ignoreUnknownValues

        public Boolean ignoreUnknownValues()
        Returns whether BigQuery should allow extra values that are not represented in the table schema. If true, the extra values are ignored. If false, records with extra columns are treated as bad records, and if there are too many bad records, an invalid error is returned in the job result. The default value is false. The value of formatOptions() determines what BigQuery treats as an extra value.
        See Also:
        Ignore Unknown Values

      • maxBadRecords

        public Integer maxBadRecords()
        Returns the maximum number of bad records that BigQuery can ignore when reading data. If the number of bad records exceeds this value, an invalid error is returned in the job result.

      • schema

        public Schema schema()
        Returns the schema for the external data.

      • sourceUris

        public List<String> sourceUris()
        Returns the fully-qualified URIs that point to your data in Google Cloud Storage. Each URI can contain one '*' wildcard character that must come after the bucket's name. Size limits related to load jobs apply to external data sources, plus an additional limit of 10 GB maximum size across all URIs.
        See Also:
        Quota

      • formatOptions

        public <F extends FormatOptions> F formatOptions()
        Returns the source format, and possibly some parsing options, of the external data. Supported formats are CSV and NEWLINE_DELIMITED_JSON.
